  <summary date="2023-03-21T16:06:29Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Korematsu-Takai Civil Liberties Protection Act of 2023 

This bill prohibits the detention or imprisonment of an individual based solely on an actual or perceived protected characteristic of the individual. The term protected characteristic includes each of the following: race, ethnicity, national origin, religion, sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, and any additional characteristic that the Department of Justice determines to be a protected characteristic.</summary>
